 spiegelten und zugleich veränderten.Untersucht werden Werke von Jules Chéret bis Théophile-Alexandre Steinlen, von Alfons Mucha bis Henri de Toulouse-Lautrec.  aFrom the romanticized ideal form to the seductive demimondaine - early French poster art courts the favor of the observer with heterogeneous images of femininity. For the first time, this study undertakes an archeology of these posters' stereotypical of images of femininity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aPosters, Frenchy19th centuryxHistory. 0aWomen in arty19th centuryxHistory. 0aWomenxPosterszFrancey19th centuryxHistory. 4a19. Jahrhundert. 4aFrankreich. 4aFrauenbild. 4aGender Studies. 4aGender. 4aJules Chéret. 4aKunst. 4aKunstgeschichte des 19. Jahrhunderts. 4aKunstgeschichte. 4aKunstwissenschaft. 7aART / History / Modern (late 19th Century to 1945).2bisacsh  a19th Century.  aArt History of the 19th Century.  aArt History.  aArt.  aFine Arts.  aFrance.  aGender Studies.  aGender.  aJules Chéret.  aWoman.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Arts, Architecture and Design 2015z9783110438642oZDB-23-DKA08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070101208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839430774zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839430774423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839430774/original  a978-3-11-070100-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2016b2016  a978-3-11-0